            <div class="pesto-pasta-ingredients">
                <h2>Pesto Pasta</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><h3>Jar Of Pesto</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Creme Fraiche</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Halloumi</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Pecorino Cheese</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Pasta (100g per person)</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Salt</h3></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="pesto-pasta-method">
                <ol>
                    <li>Heavily salt the water with sea salt. Two pinches or more should suffice. Place pasta in water and leave to boil.</li>
                    <li>Apply Olive Oil to pan and fry Halloumi until flakes of brown crispiness appear on the edges.</li>
                    <li>After pasta is cooked, drain salt water, add halloumi, add pesto, add creme fraiche and stir.</li>
                    <li>Serve with a sprinkle of pecorino on the top. </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

