        <section class="recipe-2">
            <div class="pasta-carbonara">
            </div>
            <div class="pasta-carbonara-ingredients">
                <h2>Pasta Carbonara</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><h3>Pasta</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Pancetta - 1 pack</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Grated Parmeggiano</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>2 Garlic Cloves</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>2 Egg Yolks</h3></li>
                    <li><h3>Salt & Pepper</h3></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="pasta-carbonara-method">
                <ol>
                    <li>Heavily salt the water with sea salt. Two pinches or more should suffice. Place pasta in water and leave to boil.</li>
                    <li>Crack eggs into a bowl. Rub fingers on garlic cloves. Use newly garlic-rubbed fingers to phish out egg yolks with ease and place in another bowl.
                        Whisk together with some salt and pepper and a dab of sugar.
                    </li>
                    <li>Oil a pan. Add pancetta. Chop garlic finely while pancetta is frying. Add garlic to pan when pancetta has browned and is starting to crisp.</li>
                    <li>Strain pasta water but leave a little to mix. Add whisked egg yolks, pancetta and parmeggiano. Mix throughly while heated.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

        </section>
